    "Histogram equalization is another technique to improve the contrast and enhance texture, predominantly used in satellite imagery.",
    "Adaptive histogram equalization can enhance fossil images across various modalities, including SEM and CT, facilitating better interpretation of surface topographies and internal structures.",
    "More advanced contrast adjusting techniques, as presented by Suresh et al. (2018), perform contrast enhancement while minimizing information loss.",
